          <from>MS. KARLA MACFARLANE</from>
          <p>MS. KARLA MACFARLANE : Mr. Speaker, I stand here today to speak about an issue of great importance and of personal relevance to me and to many residents of Pictou County and beyond. I grew up in Pictou West, and for as long as I have been alive the pulp mill and Boat Harbour have been a part of my daily life. As a child it was the cloud machine. It was something to be stared at in amazement crossing the Causeway. It was the place where my friends' dads worked, as well as my own father, who was employed with Canso Chemicals for 42 years.</p>
