          <p>HON. DENISE PETERSON-RAFUSE : I also want to speak on homelessness and youth homelessness, and I want to remind the member opposite that it was the NDP Government that created the homelessness outreach program, which in the first 18 months here in Halifax saw approximately 280 individuals getting homes, and now I understand it's well over 500. That is a program that is showing great success, and I'm proud that as the Minister of Community Services I could bring that to the people of Nova Scotia. (Applause)</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#044d7a53-b109-4393-8fbe-efad8b86a796">
